  <main>
    <h1>How to Play UNO</h1>

    <section>
      <h2>Objective</h2>
      <p>The goal of UNO is to be the first player to get rid of all your cards.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Setup</h2>
      <p>Each player is dealt 7 cards. The remaining cards form a draw pile, and the top card is placed face up to start the discard pile to play your cards.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Gameplay</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Players take turns playing a card from their hand to the card on top of the played pile by number, color, or symbol.</li>
        <li>If a player cannot play a card, they must draw one from the draw pile.</li>
        <li> Special cards include:</li>
        
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Skip:</strong> Next player loses their turn.
              <img src="/images/cards/red_skip.png" alt="Skip Card" class="card-image">
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Reverse:</strong> Reverses the order of play.
              <img src="/images/cards/red_reverse.png" alt="Reverse Card" class="card-image">
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Draw Two:</strong> Next player draws two cards.
              <img src="/images/cards/red_draw_two.png" alt="Draw Two Card" class="card-image">
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Wild:</strong> Can be played on any card to change the color.
              <img src="/images/cards/wild_wild.png" alt="Wild Card" class="card-image">
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Wild Draw Four:</strong> Player chooses the color and the next player draws four cards.
              <img src="/images/cards/wild_wild_draw_four.png" alt="Wild Draw Four Card" class="card-image">
            </li>
          </ul>
       
        <li>The game ends when a player deals their last card, who ever this is they are the winner</li>
      </ol>
    </section>
  </main>
